<CSSOutline-width>
<summary>
The <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS">CSS</see> <strong><c>outline-width</c></strong> property sets the thickness of an element's outline. An outline is a line that is drawn around an element, outside the <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/border">border</see>.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para>EmbedInteractiveExample("pages/css/outline-width.html")</para><para>It is often more convenient to use the shorthand property <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/outline">outline</see> when defining the appearance of an outline.</para>
<para>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/outline">outline</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/outline-color">outline-color</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/outline-style">outline-style</see><br/></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/outline-width"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
